Philippines Stocks: Atlas, Lepanto, Manila Electric, Philex

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-07-21T04:20:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/metro-pacific-philex-vista-land-philippines-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.6 percent to
4,480.01, snapping a six-day rally.  Gold producers:  Lepanto Consolidated Mining (LC)  Co.’s Class B
shares (LCB PM), which have no ownership restrictions, sank 5.3
percent to 1.25 pesos, the sharpest loss since June 13, on
speculation prices of the precious metal may slide.  Atlas
Consolidated Mining & Development (AT)  Corp fell 1.8 percent
to 24.40 pesos, snapping a two-day, 7.1 percent rally.  “Gold may see more negative pressure in the next few days
if  Europe  and the U.S. make progress” in tackling sovereign-
debt challenges, Australia & New Zealand Banking Group Ltd.
analysts wrote in a note today.  Manila Electric Co. (MER)  , the  Philippines ’ largest
power retailer, advanced 2.6 percent to 284 pesos, the highest
since Jan. 12. The utility expects sales in the first half and
for the full year to “mirror” its record 2010 performance,
Chief Operating Officer Oscar Reyes said in a phone interview
today.  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  , the nation’s biggest metals
producer, sank 5 percent to 25.65 pesos, the steepest loss since
Feb. 28. First Pacific Co. is not in talks to acquire shares of
Philex from Philippine state-run fund Social Security System,
Managing Director Manuel Pangilinan said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
